        "title": "feat(apple): add Russian and Hindi app catalogs",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe iOS and macOS apps ship inline English SwiftUI strings without app-local String Catalog resources, so Russian and Hindi cannot be selected at runtime.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd native Apple String Catalogs with a first gateway/navigation/chat/settings slice, wire the catalogs into the iOS XcodeGen target and macOS Swift Package target, and enforce complete en/ru/hi entries in CI.\n\n## User Impact\n\nThe catalog-backed iOS and macOS strings can now render in Russian and Hindi when those locales are selected. The remaining Apple surfaces, including Watch, Activity Widget, Share Extension, and the wider settings inventory, remain follow-up work.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm apple:i18n:check`\n- `pnpm test:serial test/scripts/apple-app-i18n.test.ts test/scripts/native-app-i18n.test.ts`\n- `ruby -e 'require \"yaml\"; YAML.load_file(\"apps/ios/project.yml\")'`\n- `swift package dump-package` in `apps/macos` and `apps/shared/OpenClawKit`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nAI-assisted implementation. This PR is stacked on #97110.\n",
